    <sys_ui_action action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <action_name>x_casemgmt_case_resolve</action_name>
        <active>true</active>
        <client>false</client>
        <comments>UI Action that transitions an In Progress case to Resolved status. Visible to x_casemgmt_case_manager (always) and x_casemgmt_case_agent (only when they are assigned to the case via assigned_agent or member of assigned_group, per AAP Section 0.5.6 Assigned-only rule). Delegates the all-tasks-closed check to x_casemgmt.CaseTransitionValidator.canTransitionToResolved() (single source of truth shared with ../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml). Per AAP Section 0.5.5 row 5 verbatim: "In Progress -&gt; Resolved: All linked x_casemgmt_case_task records have status = Closed - Surface 'All tasks must be closed before resolving this case.'". Surfaces verbatim error message "All tasks must be closed before resolving this case." (per AAP Sections 0.5.5 and 0.7.4) when any child task has status != Closed. Server-side-only (no client prompt) - the transition has no required parameters beyond the existing child task rows on the case. Performs the transition on the server with defense-in-depth re-validation of role, status, and "Assigned only" assignment. Surfaces a form-level blocking error via gs.addErrorMessage if any guard fails (verbatim message returned by the Script Include). Contains zero gs.eventQueue() calls per the email-disabled constraint, zero hardcoded sys_id literals, and zero PII.</comments>
